Ericsson Plans to Hire 150 at Hungary Research Center, MTI Says

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-03-10T10:19:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/ericsson-plans-to-hire-150-at-hungary-research-center-mti-says.html
Ericsson AB, the world’s largest
maker of wireless phone networks, plans to hire 150 people in  Hungary , MTI news service reported today, citing Chief Executive
Officer Hans Vestberg and Development Minister Tamas Fellegi.  Ericsson’s Hungary-based staff will expand to 1,650 by the
summer, the majority working in research and development, MTI
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest 
 agergely@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  